#compdef partykit
# ============================================================================
# partykit - real-time multiplayer applications
#             on Cloudflare Workers + Durable
#             Objects (TypeScript/Node, MIT)
#
# Author : PartyKit, Inc.
#           (founded by Sunil Pai;
#           multiplayer-app infrastructure
#           originally built at Cloudflare
#           before company spin-out)
# Upstream: https://github.com/partykit/partykit
# npm pkg : partykit
#
# `partykit` is a CLI + SDK for building +
# deploying real-time multiplayer
# applications on top of Cloudflare Workers +
# Durable Objects. PartyKit abstracts the
# Durable-Object-as-room model into a
# simpler "party" primitive where each room
# is a stateful WebSocket server backed by
# a single Durable Object instance.
#
# Architecture:
#   - **Party**: a stateful Durable Object
#     handling WebSocket connections for a
#     single room (e.g., a document, a chat
#     room, a game lobby)
#   - **Multi-party**: each room is
#     independent + globally distributed
#     (Cloudflare routes connections to the
#     nearest party instance based on
#     consistency)
#   - **Persistent state**: rooms store
#     state in the Durable Object's storage
#     API (no external database required
#     for ephemeral session state)
#   - **Hibernation**: rooms hibernate after
#     inactivity + wake on the next message
#     (cost-effective for sparse
#     workloads)
#
# Use cases:
#   - Collaborative document editors (Yjs +
#     Liveblocks-style apps via y-partykit
#     subpackage)
#   - Real-time chat rooms
#   - Multiplayer browser games (Slither.io
#     + .io game clones)
#   - Live cursors + presence indicators
#     for collaborative apps
#   - Real-time dashboards + admin panels
#     (server-pushed metrics + alerts)
#   - WebSocket-based game lobby + matchmaker
#   - AI agent coordination (party-as-agent
#     pattern; THIS CLI also has ai +
#     vectorize subcommands for AI
#     integration)
#
# Distinguishing features vs alternatives
# (Liveblocks + Ably + Pusher + Socket.IO
# servers):
#   - **Open-source first** (the entire
#     PartyKit runtime is MIT licensed)
#   - **Cloudflare-native** (deploys to
#     Cloudflare Workers; benefits from
#     CF's global edge network without
#     additional infrastructure)
#   - **No central coordinator**
#     (Cloudflare Durable Objects provide
#     consistency + global routing)
#   - **TypeScript-first** (full TS types
#     for server + client + AI helpers)
#   - **Local development** (dev command
#     uses miniflare to run Cloudflare
#     Workers locally without deploying)
#   - **Cloudflare AI + Vectorize integration**
#     (built-in commands for Workers AI
#     models + Vectorize vector DB)
#
# Usage:
#   partykit <subcommand> [args]
#
# Top-level subcommands:
#   init [name]                    - scaffold
#                                     a new
#                                     PartyKit
#                                     project
#   dev [script]                   - run a
#                                     PartyKit
#                                     project
#                                     locally
#                                     (via
#                                     miniflare)
#   deploy [script]                - deploy a
#                                     PartyKit
#                                     project
#                                     to
#                                     Cloudflare
#   list                           - list
#                                     deployed
#                                     PartyKit
#                                     projects
#   delete                         - delete a
#                                     PartyKit
#                                     project
#   info                           - show
#                                     project
#                                     info
#   tail                           - tail
#                                     real-time
#                                     logs
#                                     from a
#                                     project
#   login [cloudflare|partykit]    - login
#                                     (default:
#                                     PartyKit
#                                     auth;
#                                     or
#                                     cloudflare
#                                     for
#                                     Cloudflare
#                                     auth)
#   logout                         - logout
#                                     from
#                                     PartyKit
#   whoami                         - show
#                                     current
#                                     login
#                                     identity
#   token generate                 - generate
#                                     a token
#                                     for CI/
#                                     CD
#                                     deployments
#   env <subcmd>                   - manage
#                                     project
#                                     environment
#                                     variables
#                                     (list +
#                                     pull +
#                                     push +
#                                     add +
#                                     remove)
#   ai models                      - list
#                                     available
#                                     Cloudflare
#                                     Workers
#                                     AI
#                                     models
#   vectorize <subcmd>             - manage
#                                     Cloudflare
#                                     Vectorize
#                                     vector
#                                     DB indexes
#                                     (create +
#                                     delete +
#                                     get +
#                                     list +
#                                     insert)
#
# `init` flags:
#   -y, --yes                      - skip
#                                     prompts
#                                     (use
#                                     defaults)
#       --dry-run                  - skip
#                                     writing
#                                     files +
#                                     installing
#                                     dependencies
#   [name]                         - project
#                                     name
#
# `dev` flags:
#   -p, --port <n>                 - port to
#                                     run the
#                                     server on
#       --serve <path>             - serve
#                                     this
#                                     directory
#                                     of
#                                     static
#                                     assets
#       --https                    - enable
#                                     HTTPS
#                                     locally
#       --https-key-path <path>    - path to
#                                     HTTPS
#                                     key file
#       --https-cert-path <path>   - path to
#                                     HTTPS
#                                     cert file
#   -c, --config <path>            - path to
#                                     config
#                                     file
#                                     (partykit
#                                     .json or
#                                     partykit
#                                     .toml)
#       --compatibility-date <d>   - set a
#                                     Cloudflare
#                                     compatibility
#                                     date
#                                     (e.g.
#                                     2026-06-01)
#       --compatibility-flags <fs> - set
#                                     compatibility
#                                     flags
#                                     (repeatable)
#       --minify                   - minify
#                                     the
#                                     script
#       --live                     - enable
#                                     live
#                                     reload
#       --with-env                 - define
#                                     all
#                                     variables
#                                     in the
#                                     deployment
#       --disable-request-cf-fetch - disable
#                                     populating
#                                     request
#                                     .cf
#                                     object
#       --verbose                  - verbose
#                                     debugging
#                                     output
#       --no-hotkeys               - disable
#                                     hot keys
#                                     in dev
#                                     CLI
#
# `deploy` flags:
#       --serve <path>             - serve
#                                     this
#                                     directory
#                                     of
#                                     static
#                                     assets
#   -c, --config <path>            - path to
#                                     config
#                                     file
#       --compatibility-date <d>   - Cloudflare
#                                     compatibility
#                                     date
#       --compatibility-flags <fs> - compatibility
#                                     flags
#       --minify                   - minify
#                                     the
#                                     script
#       --with-vars                - include
#                                     all
#                                     variables
#                                     in
#                                     deployment
#       --with-env                 - define
#                                     all
#                                     variables
#                                     in
#                                     deployment
#   -n, --name <name>              - name of
#                                     the
#                                     project
#       --preview <name>           - deploy
#                                     to
#                                     preview
#                                     environment
#       --domain <domain>          - custom
#                                     domain
